source.name: SBA FranPerformance2010_v2.xlsx
source.description: An indication of franchise profitability and positive cash flow is the success and failure by franchisees to pay back their SBA-backed loans. This is a list of combined 7(a) & 504 loan performance by franchise brand. Data is based on approved loans from 10/01/01 to 09/30/10, which were assigned a franchise brand and subsequently disbursed (disbursement x $1,000) redacted to 10 or more disbursed loans from the 9 year period.
